commit_message: Correct bugs in JavaScript string escaping. Add JavaScriptConvertTest.

Json.NET 2.0 BetaNew feature - LINQ to JSON!nNew feature - Ability to specify how JsonSerializer handles null values when serializing/deserializing.nNew feature - Ability to specify how JsonSerializer handles missing values when deserializing.nChange - Improved support for reading and writing JavaScript constructors.nChange - A new JsonWriter can now write additional tokens without erroring.nBug fix - JsonSerializer handles deserializing dictionaries where the key isn't a string.nBug fix - JsonReader now correctly parses hex character codes.n

New features: Added support for deserializing to an anonymous type with the DeserializeAnonymousType method. Support for reading, writing and serializing the new DateTimeOffset type. Added IsoDateTimeConverter. Converts DateTimes and DateTimeOffsets to and from the ISO 8601 format. Added JavaScriptDateTimeConverter. Converts DateTimes and DateTimeOffsets to and from a JavaScript date constructor. XmlNodeConverter handles serializing and deserializing JavaScript constructors. Ability to force XmlNodeConverter to write a value in an array. Logic is controlled by an attribute, json:Array=true.Changes:nDates are now serialized in a JSON complient manner, similar to ASP.NET's JavaScriptSerializer or WCF's DataContractJsonSerializer - http://weblogs.asp.net/bleroy/archive/2008/01/18/dates-and-json.aspxnRemoved the AspNetAjaxDateTimeConverter.n
Change: JsonSerializer will serialize null rather than throwing an exception.

New features -New, more concise, LINQ to JSON querying syntax. -Added FromObject to JObject, JArray. -JToken WriteTo method now supports JsonConverters. -JsonSerializer supports serializing to and from LINQ to JSON objects. -JsonSerializer properly serializes IEnumerable objects. -Added Depth property to JsonReader.Changesn-Made JsonReader and JsonWriter abstract. Added JsonTextReader/JsonNodeReader and JsonTextWriter/JsonNodeWriter.n-Removed JavaScriptObject, JavaScriptArray. Replaced by LINQ to JSON objects.n
Added JsonTextReader support for NaN, PositiveInfinity and NegativeInfinity constants.
Removed old tests. Refactored DeserializeAnonymousType method.

New features: Added Skip() method to JsonReader. Skips the current JSON token and any child tokens. JsonSerializer now has the ability to populate existing members on an object. This behaviour is controlled by the ObjectCreationHandling property.Changes:nImproved behaviour of JsonReader.Depth property.nnFixes:nFloating point numbers now use ToString(r) to avoid an overflow error when serializing and deserializing a boundary value.nJsonSerializer now correctly serializes and deserializes DBNull.nJsonSerializer no longer errors when skipping a multi-token JSON structure.n
Changes: Specified CultureInfo when converting to and from strings across Json.NET.Fixes:nClone JToken when adding token with a parent to a new token.n
Added opt-in, opt-out serialization option Added virtual GetSerializableMembers to JsonSerializer

Use GetValueOrDefault() over Value when Nullable<T> known non-nullGetValueOrDefault() is an easily-inlined access to a field as thisnwill hold the correct value for both HasValue and !HasValue cases.nThe Value property in comparison contains a branch on a check that thenNullable<T> has its internal hasValue flag to decide whether to thrownInvalidOperationException or not.nnHence when a nullable type is known to have a value (not be null) andnone wants the value, rather than to possibly trigger the exception-thrownGetValueOrDefault() has a slight performance benefit over Value.nnAccordingly, replace calls to the Value property with calls tonGetValueOrDefault() when previous checks or assignments guarantee thenvalue is not null.n

Some optimisations to async reading. (#1171)MoveToContentAsync is often called in states where it will immediatelyrnreturn true without any reading. In this case return AsyncUtils.Truernavoiding allocation or async state-machine.rnrnDoReadAsync is a very heavily hit method, and can often be fulfilledrnwithout creating another state machine, so do this.rnrnThe remaining looping async case is the only use of ParsePostValueAsync,rnso inline it into the calling method, so there is one less taskrnallocation.rnrnReturn value of EatWhitespaceAsync is never used, returning void reducesrnthe number of locals an hence the size of the state-machine. Do the samernfor EatWhitespace though the impact is less.

Optimise BinaryConverter's reflection object creation. (#1177)Make the test for a type being S.D.L.Binary a single test as Binary isrna sealed class and therefore there's no need to test bases.rnrnMake the stored ReflectionObject static, reducing size and repeatedrnallocations if BinaryConverter is explicitly created by the user.

Don't explicitly check for Failed or Cancelled Statuses (#1179)Between discussion at #1137 and a few rounds of revision at #1159 wernarrived at an optimisation where tasks that are both heavily hit andrnvery likely to return in a completed state are checked for a status ofrneither RanToCompletion, Canceled or Faulted and a path is taken wherernno await is needed for any of those.rnrnThe Canceled and Faulted tasks are returned immediately, allowing thatrnstate to be passed to the caller.rnrnHowever, these are exceptional cases, and if we just continued thernsubsequent await would raise the appropriate exception. Checking forrnall three cases instead of just RanToCompletion is optimising for thosernexecptional conditions at cost (in the form of a larger comparisonrnsegment of code) to the more common cases of the task either beingrncompleted or still running.rnrnSimplify this back to a check just for RanToCompletion.

Optimise XmlNodeConverter (#1176)* Short-circuit SerializeGroupedNodes on no child nodes.rnrnAvoids creating unused Dictionary.rnrn* Don't create Dictionary in ReadAttributeElements if it'll be empty.rnrn* Reduce calls to JsonReader.TokenType virtual property.rnrn* Remove duplicate finished boolean.rnrnDifferent reasons for finishing the ReadAttributeElements loop arernnoted, but the difference isn't acted on, so merge them.rnrn* Check correct XML is from correct TokenType immediately.rnrn(This changes the exception message in the case of it also being anrninvalid objectType, but not the exception type).rn
